The issue is on line 158 with `type.toClass()`. In Java 17 with updated Javassist, the `toClass()` method returns a raw `Class<?>` which can't be automatically cast to `Class<? extends Expression>`. Let me check the rest of the file and fix this:

Good! Now let me look at the second error in `NamespaceDiscoveryImpl.java`:

The issue is on line 53: `builder.include(FilterBuilder.prefix(ns.getPackage() + "."));`. The Reflections library has been updated and the `prefix()` method is no longer static. Let me check the updated API and fix this:
